ueers' makes a significant and substantial contribution to the history of nursing and the history of sexuality, bringing together two sub-disciplines that combine only infrequently. It will be of interest to general readers as well as scholars and students in nursing, history, gender studies, and health care ethics and law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAversion therapyxHistoryx20th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aAversion therapyzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aCross-dressingxHistoryxGreat BritainxGreat Britain. 0aCross-dressingzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aGay menxHistoryx20th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aGay menzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aNurse and patientxHistoryx20th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aNurse and patientzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aPsychiatric nursingxHistoryx20th centuryxGreat Britain. 0aPsychiatric nursingzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aTransvestismzGreat BritainxHistory. 7aMEDICAL / History.2bisacsh  aBritish mental hospitals.  aGLBTIQ.  aGender equality.  aaversion therapy.  ahomosexuality.  amental health care.  amental nurses.  anurse therapists.  aoppression.  asexual deviations.  asubversive behaviours.  asubversive nurses.  asuppression.  atherapeutic optimism.  atransvestism.1 aDickinson, Tommy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499062640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784990626423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784990626/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles